"## lesson-problems.json\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"boolean-introduction\",\n  \"title\": \"Boolean Introduction\",\n  \"description\": \"Learn to use boolean variables\",\n  \"template\": \"is_warrior = True\\nis_mage = False\\n\",\n  \"solution\": \"is_warrior = True\\nis_mage = False\\n\",\n  \"entrypoint\": \"\",\n  \"inputs\": {},\n  \"time\": 1,\n  \"mode\": \"line\"\n}\n```\n\n## lesson.md\n```markdown\n# Boolean Introduction\n\nA boolean (**bool**) type in Python can have one of two values: `True` or `False`. Booleans are used to represent the truth values that are associated with the logic branches of programming.\n\nIn PythonQuest, we could use boolean values to determine the character class of our hero, Xaden. For instance, if Xaden is a Warrior, we could represent this with a boolean value:\n\n```\nis_warrior = True\n```\n\nIf Xaden is not a Mage, we could represent this as well:\n\n```\nis_mage = False\n```\n\nIn these examples, `is_warrior` and `is_mage` are variables that are set to boolean values `True` and `False` respectively. Booleans are fundamental in creating logic and conditions in Python programs, which we will explore in greater depth in later lessons.\n```\n\n## lesson-hook.ts\n```typescript\nimport { useEffect } from \"react\";\n\nimport { useLessonStore } from \"@/store/lessonStore\";\nimport { useTraceFinished } from \"@/utils/taskChecks\";\n\nimport content from \"./boolean-introduction.md?raw\";\n\nexport function useBooleanIntroduction(lessonId: string) {\n  const { startLesson, completeTask, currentTask } = useLessonStore();\n  const traceFinished = useTraceFinished();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (lessonId !== \"boolean-introduction\") return;\n    startLesson(lessonId, content, [\n      {\n        id: \"assign-boolean\",\n        title: \"Assign Boolean values\",\n        description: \"Assign boolean values to the variables\",\n      },\n    ]);\n  }, [lessonId, startLesson]);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (currentTask?.id === \"assign-boolean\") {\n      if (traceFinished) {\n        completeTask();\n      }\n    }\n  }, [currentTask, completeTask, traceFinished]);\n}\n```"